@startuml
title Admin - User Management (Create, Update, Delete)
skinparam maxMessageSize 150
autonumber

actor "Administrator" as Admin
participant "Browser (Vue SPA)" as Browser
participant "Laravel (BFF)" as BFF
participant "Entra ID (Graph API)" as EntraID
database "PostgreSQL (Local)" as DB

== Add New User ==
Admin -> Browser: Access "Add new user" form
Browser -> BFF: GET /api/admin/roles
BFF -> EntraID: Fetch available Groups/Roles
EntraID -> BFF: Role definitions
BFF -> Browser: Return form options

Admin -> Browser: Compile form (Email, Name, "Can place orders", Facilities) & Submit
Browser -> BFF: POST /api/admin/users
BFF -> EntraID: Create User / Send Invitation via Graph API
note right of EntraID: The user will configure their own\npassword upon first login via invitation
EntraID -> BFF: Success (Returns ObjectId)

opt If "Can place orders" is true
    BFF -> EntraID: Assign ordering role/group (e.g., OrderEnabled)
    EntraID -> BFF: Role assigned
end

BFF -> EntraID: Assign selected base Group (e.g. Ospedaliero-Users)
EntraID -> BFF: Group assignment confirmed

BFF -> DB: Save user profile & form data locally (Bypasses future JIT check)
BFF -> DB: Save PDV/Facilities mappings
BFF -> Browser: Display success "User added successfully"

== Update User ==
Admin -> Browser: Modify User Role or Facilities
Browser -> BFF: PUT /api/admin/users/{id}
BFF -> EntraID: Update Group Memberships (Graph API)
EntraID -> EntraID: Invalidate active Session / Token for modified user
EntraID -> BFF: Confirmed
BFF -> DB: Update Facility mappings locally
BFF -> Browser: Display success "User updated successfully"

== Delete / Disable User ==
Admin -> Browser: Delete User
Browser -> BFF: DELETE /api/admin/users/{id}
BFF -> EntraID: Disable/Delete User account (Graph API)
EntraID -> BFF: Confirmed
BFF -> DB: Mark user as deleted / inactive
BFF -> Browser: Display success "User deleted successfully"

@enduml
